cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper discusses program transformations and evolutivity in a functional language, specifically Haskell. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses software engineering concepts such as multiple views and the tyranny of the dominant decomposition, which suggests cs.SE (Software Engineering) as another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of automated transformations, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SD (Software Development). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of views in comparison to literature, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
